%N A116128 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k-4 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 3.
%C A116128 If k-4 has d digits, the concatenation is k//k-4 = 10^d*k+k-4 = m*(m+3), therefore k//k-8 = 10^d*k+k-8 = (m-1)*(m+4), so there is a large overlap (or equality) with A116105. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%Y A116128 Cf. A116105, A116122, A116129, A116143, A116259.
